<item>
            <title>[LU-3033] Remove dependency for lu_env structure in lu_cdebug_printer</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3033</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I was investigating the possibility of removing the need for an lu_env structure from ll_releasepage (as a result of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2622&quot; title=&quot;All CPUs spinning on cl_envs_guard lock under ll_releasepage during memory reclaim&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2622&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2622&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), and the first hurdle seems to be the fact that the debug infrastructure relies on this. In particular, it seems lu_cdebug_printer uses this structure to provide a temporary buffer so consecutive, non-newline terminated, calls to the print functions can be concatenated into a single message.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, unless the debug log infrastructure is reworked, I wont be able to remove the lu_env dependency. Since anything modifying the debug log code is likely to touch a lot of lines, I wanted to get some opinions on whether restructuring this would be advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is the debug logging infrastructure something that can/should be reworked to be more straight forward and simpler?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
